# ⚠️ Troubleshooting: Trust Relationship Error

## Issue
After renaming the Domain Controller computer name, authentication to Active Directory failed and I was unable to log back into the domain.

The change caused a breakdown in the secure relationship between the Domain Controller and domain authentication services.
<img width="500" height="500" alt="AD broken" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f2d7a3e7-8e67-489f-95e4-a28df3a1dcda" />

---

## Cause
- Domain Controller computer name was changed after deployment
- Active Directory dependencies and trust relationships became inconsistent
- Domain authentication could no longer complete successfully

---

- broken secure channel between client and domain


<img width="1026" height="854" alt="oldname" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0a6f9f39-4397-4815-a8c5-fbed28872a14" />
Reboot and hold f8 to enter boot menu
select 'safe mode with networking'

Login with administrator account

open the Registry Editor
In the left pane navigate to
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\SchedulingAgent
In the right pane, double click OldName

The Value Data should be the old name of your PC . . .

Control panel -> system -> rename this pc
Enter the old name and restart

